Jet Stream
Theory is that the Jet Streams come from the expansion of air from the suns heat on the side of the earth momentarily facing the Sun and from the vacuum formed by the rapid absorption of heat by cold outer space on the back side of earth.     It moves in the same direction as the earth's rotation but faster than the earth's rotation adding to the earth's rotation.
Derived from : Theories, Phenomenon and Theories,   In Search of the Jet Stream's Origin  by Raymond G Lires 11/8/99